{
  "answer": "In the poem \"Larkiyan parh rahi hain angrezi,\" Allama Iqbal observes girls learning English as a symbol of the nation's misguided embrace of Westernization. He notes sarcastically that this shift—where \"Western style is held in view\" and \"Eastern customs are deemed a sin\"—is seen as \"the path to salvation,\" and he anticipates an uncertain, dramatic outcome (\"What scene will this drama show?\").[^1]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 3*, ch. 27 (\"Larkiyan parh rahi hain angrezi\"), [p-289582](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/27-larkiyan-parh-rahi-hain-angrezi/translation/#p-289582).",
